Neuen Keycloak Credential Provider SPI fuer den device-login Credential-Typ implementieren.

Drei neue Dateien anlegen im Package dev.authsandbox.keycloak:

### 1. DeviceCredentialModel.java
Datei: keycloak-extension/src/main/java/dev/authsandbox/keycloak/DeviceCredentialModel.java

public class DeviceCredentialModel extends CredentialModel {
    public static final String TYPE = "device-login";

    // Factory - NUR die Daten die in Keycloak gespeichert werden:
    //   credentialData: publicKey + publicKeyHash (fuer Signaturpruefung in Keycloak)
    //   secretData:     encPrivKey (privater Schluessel fuer Hybrid-Decrypt)
    //   NICHT in Keycloak: encPubKey (liegt in DB Device.encPubKey)
    //   NICHT in Keycloak: deviceId (gibt es nicht mehr)
    public static DeviceCredentialModel create(
            String publicKey, String publicKeyHash, String encPrivKey) {
        DeviceCredentialModel model = new DeviceCredentialModel();
        model.setType(TYPE);
        ObjectMapper mapper = new ObjectMapper();
        model.setCredentialData(mapper.writeValueAsString(Map.of(
            "publicKey", publicKey,
            "publicKeyHash", publicKeyHash
        )));
        model.setSecretData(mapper.writeValueAsString(Map.of(
            "encPrivKey", encPrivKey
        )));
        return model;
    }

    public static DeviceCredentialModel createFromCredentialModel(CredentialModel model) {
        DeviceCredentialModel m = new DeviceCredentialModel();
        m.setUserLabel(model.getUserLabel());
        m.setType(model.getType());
        m.setCreatedDate(model.getCreatedDate());
        m.setId(model.getId());
        m.setCredentialData(model.getCredentialData());
        m.setSecretData(model.getSecretData());
        return m;
    }

    // Getter: credentialData parsen
    public String getPublicKey() { /* Jackson parse credentialData.publicKey */ }
    public String getPublicKeyHash() { /* Jackson parse credentialData.publicKeyHash */ }
    // Getter: secretData parsen
    public String getEncPrivKey() { /* Jackson parse secretData.encPrivKey */ }
}

Datenverteilung (Referenz Architektur-Dok):
  credentialData (Keycloak): { publicKey, publicKeyHash }  -- Signaturpruefung
  secretData (Keycloak):     { encPrivKey }                -- Hybrid-Decrypt
  Device.encPubKey (DB):     Base64 enc public key         -- Hybrid-Encrypt (startLogin)

WICHTIG: encPubKey und deviceId gehoeren NICHT in das Keycloak-Credential!
- encPubKey: wird in der DB gespeichert (Device.encPubKey), nicht in Keycloak
- deviceId: gibt es nicht mehr

Imports: org.keycloak.credential.CredentialModel, com.fasterxml.jackson.databind.ObjectMapper

### 2. DeviceCredentialProvider.java
Datei: keycloak-extension/src/main/java/dev/authsandbox/keycloak/DeviceCredentialProvider.java

public class DeviceCredentialProvider implements CredentialProvider<DeviceCredentialModel>, CredentialInputValidator {
    private final KeycloakSession session;

    public DeviceCredentialProvider(KeycloakSession session) { this.session = session; }

    @Override
    public String getType() { return DeviceCredentialModel.TYPE; }

    @Override
    public CredentialModel createCredential(RealmModel realm, UserModel user, DeviceCredentialModel model) {
        return user.credentialManager().createStoredCredential(model);
    }

    @Override
    public boolean deleteCredential(RealmModel realm, UserModel user, String credentialId) {
        return user.credentialManager().removeStoredCredentialById(credentialId);
    }

    @Override
    public DeviceCredentialModel getCredentialFromModel(CredentialModel model) {
        return DeviceCredentialModel.createFromCredentialModel(model);
    }

    // CredentialInputValidator - nicht verwendet fuer device-login, aber Interface erfordert:
    @Override
    public boolean supportsCredentialType(String credentialType) {
        return DeviceCredentialModel.TYPE.equals(credentialType);
    }

    @Override
    public boolean isConfiguredFor(RealmModel realm, UserModel user, String credentialType) {
        return user.credentialManager()
            .getStoredCredentialsByTypeStream(credentialType).findAny().isPresent();
    }

    @Override
    public boolean isValid(RealmModel realm, UserModel user, CredentialInput input) {
        return false; // Validation erfolgt im DeviceLoginTokenAuthenticator
    }
}

### 3. DeviceCredentialProviderFactory.java
Datei: keycloak-extension/src/main/java/dev/authsandbox/keycloak/DeviceCredentialProviderFactory.java

public class DeviceCredentialProviderFactory implements CredentialProviderFactory<DeviceCredentialProvider> {
    public static final String PROVIDER_ID = "device-login";

    @Override
